)attr default(%+$)
  $ type( input) intens(low ) just(left ) hilite(uscore)
  ~ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) hilite(reverse) color(turq)
  Ý type(output) intens(high) caps(off) just(left) pas(on) skip(on)
)Body Expand(\\)
%Tutorial -\-\~The z ISPF Git Interface (zigi)%\-\- Tutorial
%Selection ===>$ZCMD
+
                          %Finding your SSH Public Key
+
%*+From within ZIGI on the Local Repositories Panel enter the%SSH+command
%*+Select your SSH Public Key using your TN3270 emulator and copy it
+  to your workstation's clipboard.
   %*+It is now ready to be pasted into the Git server of your choice.
+
                             %Alternate approach
+
%*+Download the%.ssh/id_rsa.pub+file to your workstation from your home
+  directory. It should NOT be downloaded in binary as it is a text file.
%*+Open the file in Notepad or similar text editor.
%*+Use Control-A (in Windows) to select all to copy the key to the
+  workstation's clipboard.
  %*+It is now ready to be pasted into the Git server of your choice.
+
+
+        +Press the%Enter+key to continue your ZIGI tutorial journey.
)Init
 .cursor  = &zcmd
 &zgsr = CSR
)PROC
 &zcont = zigih710
)END
